column61:
The project aims to identify interferon stimulated genes (ISGs) downstream of the JAK/STAT pathway, induced during HCMV infection, which helps to drive virus latency. The experiment is performed in THP1 cells.

The experimental groups include:
Mock (THP1 cells only)
IFN-Beta (THP1 cells treated with IFN-B)
WT THP1 cells infected with HCMV, harvested at 1, 3 and 5 days post infection
delta IFNAR2 THP1 cells infected with HCMV, harvested at 1, 3 and 5 days post infection
delta STAT1 THP1 cells infected with HCMV, harvested at 1, 3 and 5 days post infection

The cells were harvested and RNA isolated with the traditional phenol-chloroform technique. RNA was then sent to the sequencing core facility for RNA-seq.
